{
  "texts": [
    "Other authors (Russell & Norvig, 2021, pp. 1-5) explained AI in terms of four characteristics: it thinks like a human, acts like a human, thinks rationally, and acts rationally.",
    "In another way (Paschen et al., 2020, p. 405), AI can be viewed as a computer system that acts rationally and solves problems based on the information/data it has access to/that is available to it.",
    "Specifically, AI can be explained using the input-process-output model.",
    "This means that AI receives data (input), processes it (process), and then provides other data (output).",
    "processed by AI DATA (input) NEW DATA (output) Source: authors' representation"
  ]
}